    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Heavy cord, at least 1/4 inch in diameter, formed by twisting or braiding two or more yarns of natural or artificial fiber. In ancient Egypt, rope was made from reeds or date palm fibers.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
